Accordingly to Reflection API documentation (https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Class.html#getDeclaredFields--) method Class.getDeclaredFields() "returns an array of Field objects reflecting all the fields declared by the class or interface represented by this Class object. This includes public, protected, default (package) access, and private fields, but excludes inherited fields". Class A in the below program hasn't any declared fields. So, when compiling it using the eclipse batch compiler Class.getDeclaredFields() result should be zero declared field instead of one declared field.

