false
//& something else

=> When the condition is saved, any empty lines at the end get removed. That's OK, but when the breakpoint is hit, a wrong compilation error (Syntax error, insert ";" to complete BlockStatements) is shown.

I guess the code that puts braces around the condition needs to put a line break as well.

module src {
