bug.thetext:
This code:

public class FinalNull {

	@Nullable
	private final Object value;

	public FinalNull( @Nullable Object value ){
		this.value = value;
	}

	void action(){
		if( value != null ){
			value.toString(); // Here for 'value'
		}
	}
}

Error:
Potential null pointer access: this expression has a '@Nullable' type


This should not give the warning, as the field is checked for non-null and it is final, hence cannot be null in that line.

